Dale Says Inflation May Exceed 5% Before Slowing, Mail Says

-- B y   J o h n   F r a h e r
-- 
2011-09-29T06:24:09Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-29/dale-says-inflation-may-exceed-5-before-slowing-mail-says.html
Bank of England Chief Economist
 Spencer Dale  said U.K. inflation could exceed 5 percent in
coming months before slowing “very sharply” next year, the
Daily Mail said. The newspaper cited an interview.  “My expectation is that it will rise to over 5 per cent
over the next few months and that is largely baked in the
cake,” the paper cited him as saying.   To contact the reporter on this story:
John Fraher in London at 
 jfraher@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
